ABSTRACT

This Software Project Management document presents the planning, execution, and control of CareConnect a smart hospital matching system developed to address the inefficiencies in healthcare facility selection in Ethiopia. The project aims to enable patients to find the most suitable hospital based on symptoms, budget, location, and service preferences, thereby reducing unnecessary hospital visits and treatment delays.
The document covers the full project lifecycle: feasibility analysis (technical, economic, operational, legal, and schedule), scope definition (including project charter, RTM, scope statement, and WBS), time estimation with critical path network diagram, cost estimation, resource staffing, change control strategies, and risk analysis. The project follows an incremental development lifecycle with prototyping for the matching engine.
Key deliverables include a mobile and web application with offline support, a hospital matching algorithm, user authentication, and a pilot deployment in Addis Ababa. The team consists of seven members with defined roles: Project Manager, Business Analyst, System Architect, Developer, Customer Management, Change Control Board, and Testing Team. This SPM report demonstrates the application of project management principles from initiation to closure to a real-world healthcare accessibility problem in Ethiopia. All costs are estimated in USD and converted to Ethiopian Birr at the rate of 1 USD = 157.34 ETB (May 2026).
